08/08/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Gordana Stosic, the general manager of national broadcaster Macedonia Radio and Television, stepped down on Monday (7 August), as employees staged a strike, demanding pay and other compensation that has been overdue for months now. Stosic says she has been subjected to slander by the union. (Dnevnik - 08/08/06; Makfax, A1 TV - 07/08/06)
